rmk: A flock of four birds - one adult male, one juvenile, one female and another bird I did not see properly. I have no idea what the brids were doing, they did not seem to be actively foraging and were just perched/hopping around the same area the whole time.
This was a flock of 9 birds, perching on and flying around within the canopy of tall Sal (Shorea robusta) forest.
